  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Green Climate Fund Readiness Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The programme prepared selected countries to access financing through the Green Climate Fund (GCF). The programme strengthened the recipient countries institutionally and strategically, enabling them both to plan effective and efficient uses of GCF financing, And thereafter to apply for, manage, deploy and monitor the funds. For example, it advised the target countries on the preparation of specific projects based on their national climate strategies and it did support them in developing monitoring systems in order to trace any funds deployed. The programme had been set up in the form of a trust fund and plans called for expanding its capital with money from other donors. This did allow the programme to be extended to include additional countries.</narrative>
  </description>
